'''Robert Cope''' was an actor who played a [[Wookiee warrior]] in the third [[prequel trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']],<ref name="Film">{{Film|III}}</ref> released on [[May 19]], [[2005]].<ref name="Year by Year">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref> "The Wookies Are Back!," an episode of the [[Making Episode III Webdocs]] web video series posted on [[StarWars.com]] on [[March 11]], 2005, showed Cope in his [[Wookiee]] costume with black makeup surrounding his eyes.<ref name="TWB" />

The character played by Cope was later identified as [[Eugroothwa]]<ref name="Eugroothwa">Robert Cope is the only "Robert" credited as a [[Wookiee]] in {{Film|III}}. A [[Wookiee warrior]], identified in ''[[Dressing a Galaxy: The Costumes of Star Wars]]'' as Eugroothwa, is addressed as "Robert" in "The Wookiees Are Back!". As such, Eugroothwa must be played by Robert Cope.</ref> in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] reference book ''[[Dressing a Galaxy: The Costumes of Star Wars]]'', which was written by [[Trisha Biggar]]<ref name="DAG">''[[Dressing a Galaxy: The Costumes of Star Wars]]''</ref> and released on [[October 11]], 2005.<ref name="DressingDate">{{WebCite|url=https://www.waterstones.com/book/dressing-a-galaxy-part-1/trisha-biggar/george-lucas/9780810959644|text=Dressing a Galaxy: Part 1: The Costumes of Star Wars (Hardback)|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/mxQvt|archivedate=2022-04-24}}</ref> The name brought into the current [[canon]] in the [[2017]] reference book ''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]'', which was written by [[Adam Bray]], [[Tricia Barr]] and [[Cole Horton]].<ref name="Visual Encyclopedia">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''</ref>

